<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.230049>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Ophrynopus tosensis (Tosawa & Sugihara, 1934), female: (A) head in frontal view, (B) antenna, (C) fore wing. Scale bar: (C): 0.5 mm, (A – B): 0.2 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/230049/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.230046>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Orussus melanosoma Lee & Wei sp. nov., female: (A) habitus in dorsal view, (B) head in frontal view, (C) head in dorsal view. Scale bar (A): 1 mm, (B – C): 0.2 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/230046/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.230047>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Orussus melanosoma Lee & Wei sp. nov., female: (A) head in lateral view, (B) mesoscutum and mesoscutellum, (C) hind tibia, (D) ovipositor, (E) abdomen in dorsal view. Scale bar: (D – F): 0.5 mm, (A – C): 0.2 mm. * d: discal cell, P: pterostigma." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/230047/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

